                            <comment id="13148556" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2011 16:25:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;time to add QueryProcessorTest?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13148568" author="xedin" created="Fri, 11 Nov 2011 16:50:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed. It&apos;s not related to QueryProcessor tho&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13149867" author="thepaul" created="Mon, 14 Nov 2011 20:12:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This doesn&apos;t do the right thing when minusing a negative value, like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;UPDATE validation_cf_counter SET test = test - -1 WHERE id=&apos;test_key&apos;;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It subtracts 1, instead of adding 1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13149880" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 14 Nov 2011 20:27:54 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s not related to QueryProcessor tho&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But that&apos;s the simplest way to add CQL tests I would think?  Open to other ideas.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13150746" author="xedin" created="Tue, 15 Nov 2011 20:29:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;here is the patch that fixes problem that Paul found. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Jonathan: I agree, we probably should do the same thing for CQL as we did for CLI.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13151383" author="thepaul" created="Wed, 16 Nov 2011 18:02:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 for the fix&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13151417" author="xedin" created="Wed, 16 Nov 2011 18:50:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
